==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinapic
<hw>Sin"a*pic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to sinapine; specifically, designating an acid
(<chform>C11H12O5</chform>) related to gallic acid, and obtained by the
decomposition of sinapine, as a white crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinapine</ent>⟦br⟧
